				<td colspan="2"><span>Well I just hit 41 and am killing in The Overthere again.  Most mobs still dark blue to me and compared to the beasties in Dreadlands, seem to have far less hitpoints.  
<br />

<br />
I have a little strategy and was hoping some others could give some advice.
<br />

<br />
I plan to stay in OT until 42, at which point I plan to go to Crystal Caverns to kill tentacles or possible charm Geos for phat lewtz!<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />   (and my XP of course)
<br />

<br />
I really enjoy soloing right now as my hours of play are very sparatic, and frankly have been in too many groups with my main (50 cleric) that are full of wankers.  I did try a join a group in lower guk with my bard, and in 1 hour we had 3 deaths and killed probably 4 mobs.  I realize why I enjoy solo.
<br />

<br />
Having said that, I would like to get my level up to at least 50 with my bard too so I can participate in more of our guild raids/hunts etc.  At 41, I'm not yet ready to go on most of these sorts of things.
<br />

<br />
Are there other areas I should focus on for mad XP?
<br />

<br />
I really don't want to hunt in:
<br />
Dreadlands
<br />
Dawnshrawd
<br />
GreatDivide or EW
<br />

<br />
Only because I've already been through those 4 zones so much with my bard and cleric I'm getting burned out of them.  
<br />

<br />
Any other suggestions *greatly* appreciated.  Thanks!
<br />

<br />
Lionoo Meowmixlot
<br />
41 Bard</span></td>
