				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 41 and back in Overthere, hunting for XP<a name="5793"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 28 03 12:06 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I don't know if you are at all experienced with kiting, but at 41 that's what I did. There are a great many guide threads on this and other boards for swarm kiting, but if you are looking for insane exp., you are looking in the wrong zones.
<br />

<br />
The point behind swarm kiting is you try to round up 4-12ish yellow and red mobs, yes yellow and red, and get them to kill each other for fun and profit!  What you are doing now in OT is killing mobs that next level will go light blue.  The difference in exp is STAGGERING!
<br />

<br />
Just to relate my experience after I learned to swarm, I went from 42 (maybe 41) to 52 and 5 AA points in less than a week.  I did this pre-PoP, in Tim. Deep swarming Spirocs (as many as I could get, sharing with others, normally 8 to 12).  I went from like 42 to 47 in 3 days, the exp slowed down to better than you're getting now, so I moved to Raptors in TD.  4 days of Raptors, taking the Ring island and the Statue island if available too, I hit 52 and 5 AAs. That's when I got bored with it and wanted insane exp again as it had slowed by then.
<br />

<br />
If you don't know how to swarm, read the guides and then head to EQ to swarm Ulthorks and walruses for about 3 hours until you get your feet under you, then go get real exp.
<br />

<br />
OT is nice if your 28 to 35, but it drops off noticibly after that if I remember way back to the hay-days of Kunark.
<br />

<br />
Hope that helps. If done correctly, the 40s are over before they started...
<br />

<br />
Sinfonian </span></td>
